    "subtype": "equipment",
    "text": "This sinister suit of jet-black *+1 full plate* was designed to bolster the graveknights of Yled's undead armies, creating unstoppable legions.  \n  \nThe armor gains additional abilities if it is a graveknight's armor. If a graveknight wearing undamaged *Plate of Yled* is destroyed, the armor rebuilds its body of the course of 1d10 rounds instead of 1d10 days. A living creature who dons the armor is affected by the graveknight's curse immediately instead of 1 hour.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 137,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "rare"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "e4b0e4f5f4b3d4cad3bea67ec077e297",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
            "aonid": 26,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "Recall Knowledge",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Rare",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 11,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "This rarity indicates that a rules element is very difficult to find in the game world. A rare feat, spell, item or the like is available to players only if the GM decides to include it in the game, typically through discovery during play. Creatures with this trait are rare. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creatures is increased by 5.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 1,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "00eec53f8ff824a5080c3d092eecd593",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Aberration",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 452",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 452",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 452,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Aberrations are creatures from beyond the planes or corruptions of the natural order.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "legacy",
        "game-id": "ef9980ea1619a4451a957f0fa78a5b46",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Evil",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "4.0",
              "aonid": 1,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "4.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 631",
              "aonid": 1,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 631",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Core Rulebook",
            "page": 631,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Evil effects often manipulate energy from evil-aligned Outer Planes and are antithetical to good divine servants or divine servants of good deities. A creature with this trait is evil in alignment.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 103,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Magical",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 458,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "legacy",
        "game-id": "43f6a564e13fcacc75648269d2f58f98",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Necromancy",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "4.0",
              "aonid": 1,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "4.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 634",
              "aonid": 1,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 634",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Core Rulebook",
            "page": 634,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Effects and magic items with this trait are associated with the necromancy school of magic, typically involving forces of life and death.",
        "type": "trait"
      }
    ],
